@@ -8,6 +8,18 @@ Before beginning, read the public docs on how RBAC works as a product feature:
 
 https://help.cardinalapps.io/guides/cardinal-media-server/role-based-access-control
 
+## Contexts
+
+The RBAC layer is applied in two different contexts: Media Server and Cardinal
+Cloud. The RBAC layer in each context is implemented identically with the same
+functions and helpers as described below, but the actual Capabilities and Roles
+differ.
+
+This is necessary because these two contexts have different user accounts
+assigned by different systems. In the Media Server context, `Admin` means
+something different from `Admin` in the Cardinal Cloud context, and having
+`Admin` in one does not grant you `Admin` in another.
+
 ## 1. The Core Library
 
 1. The core library is `@cardinalapps/access-control` and it can be found at
